{'identity':'Senior Director, Business Operations - Interview Thesis Brief','title':'The mandate behind the mandate','blocks':[
('callout','<b>Deliberate speed needs a commitment routing system.</b> Business Operations should shorten the distance from executive decision to observable result without becoming a process-imposing support layer.'),
('h2','ACTUAL MANDATE'),('p','Build the operating infrastructure for Engine\'s next stage of growth: company planning rhythms, resource decisions, high-stakes cross-functional execution, real-time executive visibility, a centralized pool of operators, and AI-enabled leverage.'),
('h2','WHY NOW'),('p','Engine has expanded from lodging into an all-in-one business travel and spend platform. The role posting brings planning, resource allocation, big-bet execution, dashboards, centralized operators, and AI-first efficiency into one mandate. This suggests that organizational interdependence is growing faster than the existing operating infrastructure.'),
('h2','OPERATING TENSIONS'),('table',[[ 'Tension','Risk if unmanaged','Business Operations response'],['Speed vs. precision','Fast action creates hidden rework or unclear commitments.','Make finish conditions, capacity, and intervention triggers explicit.'],['Agency vs. alignment','Functions optimize locally while enterprise priorities compete.','Preserve functional ownership inside one visible portfolio.'],['Async vs. signal integrity','Status moves out of meetings but evidence becomes stale or inconsistent.','Automate collection while exposing missing data and ownership.'],['Ambition vs. capacity','Every initiative is priority; specialist teams become the hidden constraint.','Make resource tradeoffs a named executive decision.'],['Central leverage vs. dependency','Operators become permanent staff augmentation.','Deploy against friction with an outcome and exit condition.']],[1.55*inch,2.6*inch,3.15*inch],True),
('h2','WHITE-SPACE POINT OF VIEW'),('p','Move from a calendar of planning events to a live portfolio of commitments. Each major initiative carries a small commitment contract: outcome, DRI, resource envelope, leading signals, decision date, dependencies, finish condition, and pivot/stop trigger.'),
('h2','WHAT CHANGES'),('bullets',['Leadership meetings begin with exceptions and decision questions, not slide recitation.','A priority is not considered committed until capacity and tradeoffs are visible.','Variance creates a dated intervention, not another request for status.','The centralized team leaves stronger ownership and reusable mechanisms behind.'],True)
]},
{'identity':'Senior Director, Business Operations - Interview Thesis Brief','title':'Commitment Routing System','blocks':[
('h2','THE FIVE-STAGE ROUTE'),('table',[[ 'Stage','Operating question','Required mechanism'],['1. Direction','What matters now?','Enterprise outcomes and decision boundaries'],['2. Commit','What exactly lands?','Finish condition, DRI, value hypothesis, decision date'],['3. Route','Is the bet truly funded?','Capacity, dependencies, sequencing, tradeoffs'],['4. Observe','What changes early?','Async leading signals and data-quality flags'],['5. Intervene','What decision is required?','Proceed, protect, reroute, pause, or stop']],[1.15*inch,2.25*inch,3.85*inch],True),
('h2','EXECUTIVE TELEMETRY'),('table',[[ 'Dimension','Question','Example unit'],['Portfolio focus','Is capacity tied to explicit enterprise outcomes?','Capacity share by outcome'],['Resource fit','Does funded capacity match committed scope?','Critical-role gap / dependency age'],['Delivery pace','Are outcomes moving on dated milestones?','Milestone variance'],['Decision latency','How long from variance to decision?','Elapsed days'],['Signal integrity','Can leadership trust the evidence?','Freshness / completeness / owner'],['Intervention quality','Did the decision reduce recurrence or delay?','Repeat variance / rework / cycle time'],['Adoption','Is the mechanism retained in the work?','Usage and owner compliance']],[1.45*inch,3.3*inch,2.5*inch],True),
('h2','AI-FIRST EFFICIENCY'),('p','Use AI agents to collect operating evidence, detect missing fields and stale signals, reconcile cross-system inputs, summarize variance, draft decision packets, and preserve decision history. Humans retain authority over priority, resource allocation, risk acceptance, performance judgment, and stopping decisions.'),
('h2','CENTRALIZED OPS DEPLOYMENT'),('table',[[ 'Deploy when','Do not deploy when','Exit when'],['Cross-functional ambiguity or dependency load blocks a priority.','The issue is routine functional execution with a clear owner.','Decision rights, cadence, measures, and ownership are stable.'],['Decision latency materially threatens pace or value.','The team wants an extra project manager without changing the system.','The operating mechanism is reusable and retained.'],['A high-stakes bet needs a neutral DRI and executive visibility.','The work lacks sponsorship or a real decision mandate.','The original friction and recurring variance decline.']],[2.45*inch,2.45*inch,2.45*inch],True)
]},
